  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali130-kilavi">itu piriviṭai yāṟṟāta talaiviyatu āṟṟāmai talaivaṉ vantu cārtaliṉ nīṅkiṉamai kaṇṭu vāyilkaḷ tammuḷḷē kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali130">
                <l>nayaṉum vāymaiyu naṉṉar naṭuvu</l>
                <l>mivaṉiṟ ṟōṉṟiya vivaiyeṉa viraṅkap </l>
                <l>puraitava nāṭip poytaput tiṉitāṇṭa </l>
                <l>varacaṉō ṭeṉamāynta nallūḻic celvampō</l>
                <l>ṉiraikatirk kaṉali pāṭoṭu pakalcelak </l>
                <l>kallātu mutirntavaṉ kaṇṇillā neñcampōṟ</l>
                <l>pulliruḷ parattarūum pulampukoṇ maruṇmālai;</l>
                <l rend="space">immālai, </l>
                <l>aiya raviraḻa leṭuppa varōveṉ </l>
                <l>kaiyaṟu neñcaṅ kaṉaṉṟutī maṭukkum;</l>
                <l rend="space">immālai, </l>
                <l>iruṅkaḻi māmalar kūmpa varōveṉ </l>
                <l>ṉarumpaṭar neñca maḻivoṭu kūmpum;</l>
                <l rend="space">immālai,</l>
                <l>kōvalar tīṅkuḻa liṉaiya varōveṉ </l>
                <l>pūveḻi luṇkaṇ pulampukoṇ ṭiṉaiyum; </l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku,</l>
                <l>paṭucuṭar mālaiyoṭu paitaṉō yuḻappāḷaik </l>
                <l>kuṭipuṟaṅ kāttōmpuñ ceṅkōlāṉ viyaṉṟāṉai </l>
                <l>viṭuvaḻi viṭuvaḻic ceṉṟāṅkavar </l>
                <l>toṭuvaḻit toṭuvaḻi nīṅkiṉṟāṟ pacappē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="2">While lamenting “these are the ones that appeared through him:</l>
                <l corresp="1">longing, truthfulness and a good middle(?),</l>
                <l corresp="5">as the day goes along with the sinking of the sun with rays in rows,</l>
                <l corresp="4">like this wealth from a good turn that vanished like with a king</l>
                <l corresp="3">who ruled sweetly, destroying falsehood, much studying greatness,</l>
                <l corresp="7">in lonely obscure evening when bleak darkness spreads </l>
                <l corresp="6">like in the heart that is without eyes of one who aged without learning,</l>
                <l>This evening,</l>
                <l>when the lords raise shining fires, ah, my</l>
                <l corresp="8-10">prostrate heart will glow [and] kindle a fire.</l>
                <l>This evening,</l>
                <l>when the big blossoms close, ah, in the dark backwaters, my</l>
                <l corresp="11-13">heart in difficult affliction will close with desolation,</l>
                <l>This evening,</l>
                <l>when the cowherds despair on [their] sweet flutes, ah, my</l>
                <l corresp="14-16">flower-grace kajal eyes will despair with loneliness.</l>
                <l corresp="17">That is to say,</l>
                <l>her who bears suffering pain from the sinking sun and the evening</l>
                <l>pallor will leave just by the way of his touch,</l>
                <l>like the vast army of him with a just sceptre who guards [and] protects the hamlets</l>
                <l corresp="18-21">will go just by the way of leaving.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
